text.text: roll into base

text: Rolling into the base rate is a payer requirement set at the Policy or Benefit plan levels. To enable it: 1. Click Admin > Billing > Payers 2. Click the payer name 3. You can turn on rolling into the base from the policy or benefit level by clicking on the Requirements field and selecting Roll supplies and additional services into the base rate charge.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=moq6utfcqw

text.text: How do I roll into base?

text: To roll into base, you can click on the Requirements field and select Roll supplies and additional services into the base rate charge.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=moq6utfcqw

text.text: Explain rolling into base

text: When you set this feature as a payer requirement, itemized charges will be rolled into the base rate. For example, if your base rate is 1100, you can combine the itemized charges resulting in a base rate of 1300.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=moq6utfcqw

text.text: How to select the rate category?

text: To select the rate category, you can click the Charges tab and then the Charge category field. The rates will be applied to the HCPCS for the claim.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=lhnjkg7ojt

text.text: How to automatically apply U1/U2 modifier first?

text: To automatically apply the U1/U2 modifier first, you can go to the Modifiers tab and then the Modifier application settings. You can also apply the TN modifier to claims with rural or super-rural origin.

text.text: How to set and use ICD-10 Favorites?

text: To set up ICD-10 favorites, you can manually create a list by following these steps: 1. On the navigation bar, select **Settings** 2. On the Settings page, click the **Diagnosis favorites** tab 3. On the search field, enter a partial description or the ICD-10 code 4. As you type, a list appears 5. Select the code from the list 6. The code displays under the search bar 7. Adding a nickname to the code is optional but if done, allows users to search for codes using the nickname when assigning codes to a claim.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=f6fj0yksql

text.text: How to move an account to collections?

text: To move an account to collections, you can follow these steps: 1. On the navigation bar, click **Claims** and then **Patient Billing**. 2. On the tab you select, scroll down to find the account or enter the patient name in the box under the column heading. 3. Click the check boxes to the right of the patient name. 4. Click **Move to collections**. 5. You will see a message confirming the successful move of the accounts.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=vmk2dlthc0

text.text: How do I move an account to collections?

text: To move an account to collections, you can follow these steps: 1. Hover over **Claims** on the navigation bar and select **Patient Billing**. 2. Depending on the account's status, click either the **Final statement sent** or **Collection letter sent** tab. 3. A list of accounts display in the grid. To select: a. One account: Check the box next to the patient's name on the list. b. Multiple accounts: Check the box next to the name of each patient until all accounts are selected. c. All accounts: Check the box at the top of the grid next to "Patient name". 4. Click **Move to collections**.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=vmk2dlthc0

text.text: explain self service

text: Self service is a way for customers to manage their accounts without having to contact a customer service representative. Some examples of self service options include: online banking, bill pay, and account inquiries.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=sjqwdr2fs6

text.text: use dashboard?

text: The Dashboard is a powerful tool that offers a wide range of features and functionalities. It is the first page you land on when you log onto ZOLL Billing. You can easily access claims you worked on today, create or enter work flows for incomplete, follow-up, and denied claims, and view import issues that need your attention.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=2v5tp531v2
